First version of Send SMS Script for PowerShell. 
you will need a valid gateway account with PSWinCom (www.pswin.com)


############
SendSMS.ps1:
############
is a simple example. it uses string replacement on an existing XML String and submitts that to the PSWinCom Gateway





#####################
SMS_SendMultiple.ps1:
#####################
uses a Custom object to store messages before submitting. 
This way you can build a list of messages to be submitted, i.e use Get-Content from a Text File.
the properties that are mandatory is Receiver and Message_text 

Store the message objects in a Hashtable then send the hashtable along with your username and password to the BuildXML function
The resulting XML can be used ( outerxml in string format ) to submit messages to the PSWinCom Gateway